# How to Get Started
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. Copy this file to .env: cp .env.example .env
# 2. Get API credentials from https://my.telegram.org/apps
# 3. Fill in TELEGRAM_API_ID and TELEGRAM_API_HASH
# 4. Generate session string: python session_string_generator.py
# 5. Fill in TELEGRAM_SESSION_STRING with the generated value
# 6. Never commit your .env file to version control
